item.description:
Rouge provides lots of different code block &quot;hints&quot;. If you leave off the hint, it tries to guess and sometimes gets it wrong. These are just a few hints that we use often.
Variables If your example contains a placeholder value that's subject to change, use the format &lt;[A-Z_]+&gt; for the placeholder value: &lt;MY_VARIABLE&gt;
export name=&lt;MY_NAME&gt; This syntax is reserved for variable names, and will cause the variable to be rendered in a special color and font style.
